HEADWORD: Preservation
<hw>Pres`er*va"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧servation</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act or process of
preserving, or keeping safe; the state of being preserved, or kept from
injury, destruction, or decay; security; safety; <as>as,
<ex>preservation</ex> of life, fruit, game, etc.</as>; a picture in good
<xex>preservation</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Give us particulars of thy <qex>preservation</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

